14/02/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis announced plans Monday (13 February) to strengthen legislation related to telecommunications security. 
Earlier in the day, he met with managers of the state telecom and postal services regulators about an unprecedented phone-tapping scandal in the country. 
According to Karamanlis, the government plans to increase financing and expand the power of state regulators in issues related to telecom security.
In other news Monday, international media reported that Greece is the EU's worst offender when it comes to implementing Union laws. 
The European Court of Justice found the Greek government failed to comply with EU directives in 20 cases last year. 
(ANA, MPA, UPI - 13/02/06)
